# JavaScript Performance Optimization Tips

Performance matters. Every millisecond counts when it comes to user experience and SEO rankings.

## Key Optimization Techniques

### 1. Code Splitting

Divide your code into smaller chunks and load only what's needed:

```javascript
// Bad: All code in one file
import { heavyFeature } from './heavy.js';

// Good: Dynamic import when needed
const module = await import('./heavy.js');
```

### 2. Lazy Loading

Defer loading resources until they're actually needed:

```javascript
const img = new Image();
img.addEventListener('load', () => {
  document.body.appendChild(img);
});
img.src = 'large-image.jpg';
```

### 3. Debouncing and Throttling

Prevent excessive function calls:

```javascript
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => fn(...args), delay);
  };
}
```

## Measuring Performance

Use browser tools:

- Chrome DevTools Performance tab
- Lighthouse for audits
- Web Vitals for real-world metrics

Optimization is an ongoing process. Monitor, measure, and improve continuously.

# Mastering CSS Grid for Modern Layouts

CSS Grid is one of the most powerful layout tools available. It enables complex, responsive designs with minimal code.

## Grid Basics

Define a grid container:

```css
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-template-rows: auto;
  gap: 2rem;
}
```

## Responsive Grids

Create layouts that adapt to different screen sizes:

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .grid-container {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
```

## Advanced Techniques

### Auto-Fit and Auto-Fill

```css
.auto-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 1rem;
}
```

This creates a responsive grid that adjusts the number of columns based on available space.

## Grid Areas

Name your grid areas for more semantic layouts:

```css
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header"
    "sidebar main"
    "footer footer";
}
```

## Conclusion

CSS Grid transforms how we approach web layouts. Start experimenting today!
